):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25346695/247053_Kia_EV9_AHawkins_0001.jpg 750w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/828x552/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25346695/247053_Kia_EV9_AHawkins_0001.jpg 828w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/1080x720/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25346695/247053_Kia_EV9_AHawkins_0001.jpg 1080w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/1200x800/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25346695/247053_Kia_EV9_AHawkins_0001.jpg 1200w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/1440x960/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25346695/247053_Kia_EV9_AHawkins_0001.jpg 1440w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/1920x1280/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25346695/247053_Kia_EV9_AHawkins_0001.jpg 1920w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/2048x1365/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25346695/247053_Kia_EV9_AHawkins_0001.jpg 2048w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/2400x1600/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25346695/247053_Kia_EV9_AHawkins_0001.jpg 2400w\" src=\"https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/2400x1600/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25346695/247053_Kia_EV9_AHawkins_0001.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"responsive\"/\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003ePhoto by Andrew J. Hawkins / The Verge\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"zephr-anchor\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eFive electric vehicles from Hyundai, Kia, and Genesis now qualify for the US’s $7,500 EV tax credit, \u003ca href=\"https://electrek.co/2025/01/02/hyundai-kia-evs-qualify-7500-tax-credit-first-time/\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eElectrek\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e reports. The new models include popular vehicles like the Hyundai Ioniq 5 crossover SUV and Kia EV9 three-row family hauler. Now, 25 EVs and plug-in hybrids across 10 brands \u003ca href=\"https://fueleconomy.gov/feg/tax2023.shtml\"\u003equalify for the credit\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Biden Administration’s EV tax credit rules \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/8/26/23323115/ev-tax-credit-foreign-automaker-hyundai-wto-discriminate\"\u003emandate\u003c/a\u003e building vehicles in North America for eligibility and include \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23310457/inflation-reduction-act-ev-tax-credit-act-explainer-how-to#:~:text=What%20are%20the%20battery%20requirements%20in%20the%20new%20EV%20tax%20credits%3F\"\u003eadditional requirements for sourcing battery components\u003c/a\u003e. In 2022, Hyundai and Kia \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/8/26/23323115/ev-tax-credit-foreign-automaker-hyundai-wto-discriminate\"\u003ethreatened to take legal action\u003c/a\u003e against Biden’s Inflation Reduction Act after it expanded the available credits but left the EVs they were building in Korea ineligible for them.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eNow that Hyundai has opened up a $7.6 billion EV \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24163520/hyundai-randy-parker-interview-ev-sales-ioniq-sales\"\u003emanufacturing plant in Georgia\u003c/a\u003e to produce the \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/3/24235272/hyundai-2025-ioniq-5-tesla-nacs-ev-charging-supercharger\"\u003eNACS-equipped 2025 Ioniq 5\u003c/a\u003e and the \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/20/24301740/hyundai-ioniq-9-three-row-electric-suv-laas\"\u003eupcoming Ioniq 9\u003c/a\u003e three-row SUV, its vehicles are eligible.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv role=\"button\" aria-label=\"Zoom\" tabindex=\"0\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"List of vehicles that qualify for $7,500 credits with up to $80,000 MSRP limit includes Genesis GV70, Ioniq 5, Ioniq 9, EV6, and EV9.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1023px) 100vw, 744px\" srcset=\"https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/376x223/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 376w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/384x228/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 384w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/415x246/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 415w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/480x285/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 480w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/540x320/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 540w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/640x380/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 640w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/750x445/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 750w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/828x491/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 828w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/1080x641/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 1080w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/1200x712/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 1200w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/1440x854/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 1440w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/1920x1139/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 1920w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/2048x1215/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 2048w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/2400x1424/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png 2400w\" src=\"https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:1982x1176/2400x1424/filters:focal(991x588:992x589):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25814413/Screenshot_2025_01_02_at_3.39.00_PM.png\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\"/\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cem\u003eHyundai, Kia, and Genesis models have been added to the Federal Tax Credits list as of January 1st, 2025.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e \u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eScreenshot: The Verge\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eHowever, Hyundai and Kia might lose the benefit if the upcoming Trump administration makes drastic changes. The President-elect vowed during his campaign to eliminate the EV incentives \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/6/24289494/trump-election-electric-vehicle-tax-credit-tesla-elon-musk\"\u003eon “day one,”\u003c/a\u003e though American automakers have \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/21/24302592/trump-ev-tax-credit-auto-alliance-av-framework\"\u003epleaded to let it live\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eBut unless Congress votes to eliminate the program, Hyundai and Kia buyers could still get the incentive for the 2025 tax year or take advantage of it through a lease. \u003ca href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/11/15/climate/electric-vehicles-trump-tax-credit.html\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eThe New York Times\u003c/em\u003e recently reported\u003c/a\u003e that Trump could try to take other actions without Congress by eliminating the credit for leases or taking down websites with information about the program.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eMost Popular\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eMost Popular\u003c/p\u003e\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/1/24333612/cybertruck-fire-explosion-trump-hotel-las-vegas\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eOne dead, seven injured as Cybertruck explodes outside Trump’s hotel in Las Vegas\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003chr/\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/1/24330191/popeye-tintin-head-2025-public-domain\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003ePopeye and Tintin are now in the public domain\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003chr/\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/2/24334268/apple-siri-recording-privacy-lawsuit-settlement-proposed\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eApple will pay $95 million to people who were spied on by Siri\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003chr/\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com